Japan’s Jogmec Invests About $55 Million in South African Platinum Project

-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 
2011-08-17T08:09:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/japan-s-jogmec-invests-about-55-million-in-south-african-platinum-project.html
Japan Oil, Gas & Metals National
Corp. invested 4.2 billion yen ($55 million) in an  Itochu Corp. (8001) 
platinum, palladium and nickel project in  South Africa ,
according to a statement today on the state-run agency’s
website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
